-- Ex-Goldman China Head Hu Says 20% Yuan Gain Won't Hurt Economy, Hexun Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-28T00:07:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/ex-goldman-china-head-hu-says-20-yuan-gain-won-t-hurt-economy-hexun-says.html

          
          
             A Chinese currency appreciation of
20 percent over the next two to three years won’t hurt the
Chinese economy as exports have remained strong, Fred Hu,
formerly Goldman Sachs Group Inc.’s Greater China Chairman, told
Hexun.com in an interview.  
